Whoops - Forgot to list the AlphaLab website for submitting applications for the Winter 2010 class:   www.alphalab.org
AlphaLab is a great resource for entrepreneurs. Great companies from Carnegie Mellon, Pitt, Duquesne and more can benefit from AlphaLab
Applications for the winter 2010 AlphaLab class are due on October 30th.  There were 100 apps for 6 slots last class, so get yours in early!
Another great AlphaLab class graduates today!  The quality of ideas and companies is really strong and is getting better and better.
Zipano put control of privacy in the user's hands - and that is unique.  Their first market is location based services.
The final presenter @ AlphaLab Demo Day3 is Zipano.  Zipano solves the privacy problem in social network info sharing.
Another AlphaLab alum, Skill-Life, is in the house.  CEO Felix Brandon Lloyd has done a great job bringing financial literacy to teens.
the Vivo CEO, Paul Fireman, wants an "Invest Now" button so remote investors can wire their investment!  :-)
Vivo is actually broadcasting AlphaLab Demo Day3 live.  Potential investors are watching from all over the country.
Vivo is on deck @ AlphaLab Demo Day3. They have a unique live video streaming platform.  Check them out at www.vivolive.com
Next up @ AlphaLab Demo Day:  NavPrescience. They have nextgen GPS apps that incorporate prediction and personalization.
AlphaLab alumnus Crono got follow-on investment from InnovationWorks and an SBIR from the National Science Foundation - WOW!
CloudFab also helps job shops and contract manufacturers make more money by utilizing machine downtime.   Helping both sides: way cool
still thinking about CloudFab @ AlphaLab Demo Day3.  They are helping hackers and makers realize their mass customization dreams.
Jim Jen introduced AlphaLab alumni companies:  Blendrhouse, Chogger, Crono and Skill-Life.  All are kicking butt and taking names!
SmackBots is LeftRight's 1st iPhone app. check them out at www.leftrightstudios.net
Rockem Sockem - LeftRight Studios knocks out the competition in multiplayer games: 3rd today @ AlphaLab Demo Day3
all hackers and college students need the convenience of ordering food on-demand.  Fooala makes it dead simple to order your heart's desire
up next at AlphaLab Demo Day 3 -  Fooala.  Fooala has created an open online ordering platform for restaurants that deliver.
Nick Pinkston, CEO of CloudFab is really knocking it out of the park.  Great lead-off for AlphaLab Demo Day 3!
Up first at AlphaLab Demo Day 3 - CloudFab.  CloudFab is a really cool mass customization marketplace.
AlphaLab Demo Day 3 is kicking-off.  Jim Jen has done a great job creating a excellent environment to incubate capital efficient start-ups

@alphalab Demo Day 2 has been a big success.  The 2nd class of 6 companies is impressive.  Can't wait to see the next class (apps due 5/15)
Resumator has launched and attracted customers all in less than 20 weeks!  Now that is capital efficiency - @alphalab is really effective
The capstone presentation @alphalab Demo Day - Don Charlton, CEO of Resumator, taking the pain and paper out of hiring - very timely ...

Josh Albrecht and Matt Kaniaris are off and running with BitBlinder.  These @alphalab Demo Day presentations are off-the-charts good.  WOW!
BitBlinder "micropayments" - SETI for the rest of us.  They can do it 10 times cheaper than Annonymizer - sign me up!!
BitBlinder leads off after the break for @alphalab Demo Day. A better, cheaper way for businesses/consumers to protect their privacy online
